OL,3,CHomelessness crisis the 'worst it has
OL,4,Cbeen for a long time'
OL,6,FHe told us that people have tried to
OL,7,Fsteal a rucksack he uses as a pillow
OL,8,Fand has watched his friend's sleeping
OL,9,Fbag being stolen.
OL,11,FCouncillor Paul McCusker told UTV the
OL,12,Fcity is becoming more dangerous.
OL,14,F"It's getting more difficult to keep
OL,15,Fpeople safe and keep people alive," he
OL,16,Fsaid.
OL,18,F"Outreach services here are a lifeline
OL,19,Fto many people who are homeless here
OL,20,Fin the city, but they are stretched."
